channel.title: Really cool :) (My B-day Present) Suzuki Moped (NEW VID! May 28, 2010)
channel.description:
Well this is my new moped I got today from my 19th b-day (not for another 4 days -May 31) I just wanted to show you guys :) Today I maxed the speed at about 75 mph, I got an alarm on it that sounds hella funny lol. Its motorized and electric, cost $8,699 brand new. I put a $6,500 down payment so I owe $2,199 more. [b]88 miles per gallon[/b] :) Here are some pix [size=18pt][u][i][b]Well thanks for checking it out guys! Tell me what you think![/b][/i][/u][/size] :)
Vid: http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=-eCkMpdnxng
Pix: [IMG]http://i344.photobucket.com/albums/p348/tekidder_2008/scooter/DSCN0267.jpg[/img] [IMG]http://i344.photobucket.com/albums/p348/tekidder_2008/scooter/DSCN0264.jpg[/img] [IMG]http://i344.photobucket.com/albums/p348/tekidder_2008/scooter/DSCN0263.jpg[/img] [IMG]http://i344.photobucket.com/albums/p348/tekidder_2008/scooter/DSCN0262.jpg[/img]
[size=18pt][u][i][b]Well thanks for checking it out guys! Tell me what you think![/b][/i][/u][/size] :)

Wow nice.

lawl, i c it charging.

electricity vehicles are weird.

Its a moped, not a enviromental friendly box car.

[/quote]Thanks man Its hella fun. I was riding down the freeway and hit 75 mph, but i didnt want to get pulled over so I went back down to 60 lol

-.- Pansy ass, tickets are fun to deal with. Or even, taking off through the woods on a quad, and out-running the police.

@TOPIC - Not bad, I have a 150cc sitting in my garage, that is actually not able to be registered, so it was a pointless buy, so im now working on getting my Aunts 600cc moped (automatic trans on both myn and hers :))

It looks nice, but i dont like the colors of it

EDIT: Happy early b-day btw, I just noticed that part :)[/quote]Thanks coon, and yeah Im working on the colors. I’m scheduled to get a new paint job for it this weekend
